1.Weeks 1-2: Protocol Bridging and Flow Control:Target: SpaceWire (ECSS-E-ST-50-52C) to 

AXI4-Stream.
Terrestrial video pipelines rely on continuous backpressure via TREADY. In space payloads, you bridge directly to SpaceWire or SpaceFibre networks.

Task: Study the ECSS-E-ST-50-52C standard. Deep dive into the Link Management FSM, focusing on the strict transition states between ErrorReset, Connecting, and Run.

Deliverable: Write a synthesizable VHDL module bridging a native 8-bit SpaceWire receiver interface to a 32-bit AXI4-Stream master interface.

Architectural Constraint: Your bridge must handle credit-based flow control (FCT tokens) dynamically. Defend how you prevent FIFO overflow on the AXI side when a disconnect occurs mid-packet without losing the current Earth Observation (EO) frame boundary.